                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="shipment">#</a> What if the shipment does not passan Ant Commodity inspection?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    If an inspection fails for any reason, Ant Commodity will not release the funds to
                    the producer nor send the shipment to buyer. Ant Commodity will send the shipment
                    inspection report to the producer and buyer at the same time, along with information about
                    the discrepancies.
                    <br><br>
                    Ant Commodity will coordinate with both sides to come to a decision. If an agreement cannot
                    be reached, Ant Commodity will cancel the contract and return the full amount (excluding bank
                    charges) to the buyer. We will not charge the 0.5% fee if a contract is cancelled
                    because of a fault on the part of the producer.

                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="whoShip">#</a> Who ships the consignment?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    Ant Commodity sends the shipment to the buyer, not the producer. We
                    have a team of experts that handles the shipping.
                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="payment">#</a> What are Ant Commodity’s payment terms and methods?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    For payments of less than $2000, Ant Commodity accepts online payments. For each online payment,
                    there will be a 3.5% transaction fee.  Ant Commodity must receive the payment in full
                    to execute the service.
                    <br><br>
                    For payments over $2000, Ant Commodity will send the banking information for a t/t
                    transaction(wire transaction). There will be a $45 fixed bank fee for each
                    transaction. Ant Commodity must receive the payment in full to execute the service.
                    Note:All bank charges are charged to the buyer’s account.
                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="creditCard">#</a> Is my credit card and bank details safe?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    We do not store your credit card details on our servers. We use third-party
                    services to process your transaction, and each time you send us a payment, you will
                    need to submit your card details.
                    <br><br>
                    We may ask for your bank number or T/T receipt to confirm the payment. As the information
                    will be transferred through our messaging app, the information will be stored for up to
                    two years. We use the highest-level SSL encryption technology to secure all messages and transactions.
                    <br>
                    If we haven’t addressed your question here, please send us a message. We will get back to you within 24 hours
